      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey so i'm running a linear regression for some housing price predictions but my residual plots look really weird. the errors dont seem to be normally distributed at all, there are some heavy tails and it's definitely not a bell curve. what's the best way to handle this if i need to stick to a linear framework?",
