      "content": "thanks for the tip. i tried a log transform but it didn't really fix the extreme outliers i'm seeing in the tails. it's like there are these specific data points that are just way off from the rest of the distribution, making the whole model feel unreliable. is there a way to identify or treat those specific points without just deleting them?",
