      "content": "Instead of outright deletion, you can employ robust regression methods, such as using M-estimators or Huber loss functions, which down-weight the influence of extreme outliers. Alternatively, you could carefully investigate the source of those outlier data points; perhaps they represent a different market segment requiring a categorical indicator variable in your model. If they truly represent measurement errors, capping or winsorizing the extreme values can also stabilize the model without losing all the data.",
